t</span><br>  Posts: 541<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 1:59:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> It seem in the last few weeks that many of us have become experts at camping the boards and posting right at 12:00:00 and nailing the day.  Only to find out a few minutes later that another person posted at the same time.  So, Adune ends up rolling the date between those that posted at 12:00:00.<br>
<br>
Is it time that we find a better solution to this?  This is what I would consider board camping at it's finest.  Honestly, this problem is only going to get worse, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
