53rd Enchantress <p><img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959014.jpg"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 1335<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 2:32:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> /agree Sadara.<br>
<br>
I'd like to see a rules stating:<br>
<br>
An Indy/Guild may only sign up once per date.  If there are multiple posts for the same date, they will be deleted.<br>
<br>
When signing up for a date, the subject must contain the date &amp; start time.<br>
<br>
It's annoying to deal with 3 posts because someone was timing their clock to board time exactly.  If you want to board camp, fine.  But if you post early, that's it.  Maybe we'll see less camping of 12:00:00 if people know than an early post will mean they can't signup for the date.  It would also make it impossible for multiple guild members to camp the same date to increase chances.<br>
<br>
Re: Start time, it's helpful for the people signing up, and for mods.  We know right away if a time zone conflict will exist or not.  The way it is now, people can sign up for dates, get posted to calendar, and then post start times that conflict with each other.  Unless I check the posts of people that didn't include a start time daily, it's quite possible that time zone conflicts could slip through, and screw up a raid.  <br>
<br>
But whatever, it doesn't matter.  Too many people would oppose those changes. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune2.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 2:39:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> I would defintely like to see how things change when Fear and Hate get increased. If there are a substantial number of mobs.. or they also get harder, some of the traditional &quot;in and out in 5 hours&quot; crews may not be able to do it.<br>
<br>
If that happens, you could have an increase demand on the weekends.  <br>
<br>
I really hope that's not the case.. I am kinda partial to getting in and out of hate or fear in 5 hours or less.<br>
<br>
I would be interested in seeing what other methods could be suggested to avoid board camping.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualvimar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alvimar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 2:53:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> /agree Adune, worth bringing up again though and sound arguments I think.<br>
<br>
From what I've been hearing (all heresay at this point) the upper areas are what are being buffed a lot more so raiding the lower section could still mean a 5 hour to folks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1928<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 3:04:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> The 3 week thing may be a good start in helping.  Someone did some statistics on indys and guilds and how often they raided the planes.  Only good argument I can see for not extending it to 3 weeks is that you may end up getting people to plan so far ahead, they either forget or the people signing up may not even be valid anymore.  May be worth a try and then see how it goes to make sure the raids are happening.   Maybe since fear is in such a demand, if a guild hosts hate, they shouldn't be able to host fear in the 2 week alottment?  Hate doesn't seem to have as much of a demand so doing it the other way may leave hate open more than it should be.  /shrug<br>
<br>
I do think there should be a rule on what goes in the first post.  Granted we don't always know the start time at first, but I've seen too many posts without atleast a guild tag or indy statement so who knows who is posting for whom.  <br>
<br>
As for having a rule of multiple posts, this doesn't appear to be an epidemic (how often does this happen really?) from what I've seen.  I don't think it is right that if someone posts first and it doesn't hit the time right, they shouldn't be allowed to post again.  Sometimes they could have the date wrong on what they are posting for and hit it a day early..they shouldn't be penalized.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Saph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 1900<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 4:06:33 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/itsme.jpg height=153 width=142></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> i'm sickened that random is used for this calendar, that should be a clue to anyone that there are serious problems with it and it's not feasible <p>nillon<br>
