<br>
Sadara - Planning an evenning of my life two weeks ahead for a video game is bad enough. I really don't want to have to do it three weeks in advance. The alternative of course would be to sign up for things and then if I happen to make plans that night or have to do something work related, just not show up for the raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uqualtarshylok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qualtar Shylok</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 6:47:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://fp.geocities.com/blood_inferno/images/QualtarShylok.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Board Camping, we have been expert at it!!</span><hr size=1> Our guild (Blood Inferno) recently signed up at exactly 12:00am the same time a poster from Watchers (Barrin) signed up.  Just a few posts on our guild board were made recently, but the jist of what we thought of was to just share the raid.  It seemed like the thing to do.  I don't know what the raid leaders decided (if they have decided anything yet) as I am not running the raid.<br>
<br>
